            "section": "great_pillar",
            "speaker": "pixel",
            "speaker_mode": "narration",
            "text": "The Great Pillar's heart chamber was nothing like the tourist observation decks five hundred feet above. Down here, at the root, the Pillar wasn't smooth black stone. It was alive with geometric patterns flowing like water, pulsing with light that seemed to exist in more dimensions than I had names for.",
            "direction": null,
